00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:33,400
Hello. Oh, sorry. Excuse me.

233
00:23:33,600 --> 00:23:36,600
I was.... You had
a "Help Wanted" sign out there?

234
00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:41,000
Hey, Vijay, uncle!
Someone's here for the job.

235
00:23:41,400 --> 00:23:45,000
Raj, I'm right here.
There's no need to yell, son.

236
00:23:45,800 --> 00:23:48,400
-So you're looking for a job, huh?
-Yes, sir.

237
00:23:49,400 --> 00:23:51,600
You ever pump gas before?

238
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:53,600
No, sir.

239
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:56,800
Well, that's all right, because
we don't have any gas pumps.

240
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:03,400
Right?

241
00:24:05,600 --> 00:24:08,000
You seem like a good guy.
You got the job.

242
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:12,000
You start tomorrow morning, 8 a.m.
Minimum wage.

243
00:24:12,600 --> 00:24:15,400
That's okay, it's great.
I'll be here a half-hour early then.

244
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:18,200
-Thank you very much.
-You're very welcome.

245
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:20,800
Thanks a lot.

246
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:24,000
-Sorry. Sorry about that.
-It's cool. It's all right.

247
00:24:24,200 --> 00:24:26,800
-Don't worry about it.
-Okay. Bye-bye.

248
00:24:28,400 --> 00:24:30,600
-Not a problem.
-Not a problem? Okay.

249
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:35,000
-Clumsy fellow, huh?
-Shit happens.

250
00:24:35,200 --> 00:24:36,600
I like him.

251
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:40,400
<i>Papá</i>, please eat your food.

252
00:24:43,400 --> 00:24:46,400
I thought we were going out.
Why aren't you dressed yet?

253
00:24:47,800 --> 00:24:50,200
I don't think I should leave him.

254
00:24:50,400 --> 00:24:53,200
Come on. He's gonna be fine.

255
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:57,600
You don't do anything anymore except
study and worry about your dad.

256
00:24:58,400 --> 00:25:00,800
You're turning into a geek.

257
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:04,200
Are you gonna be all right
without me, <i>Papá?</i>

258
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:07,800
Sure, <i>mija.</i> You go out and have fun.

259
00:25:10,600 --> 00:25:12,600
Okay, I'm gonna change really fast.

260
00:25:21,400 --> 00:25:23,800
Come on, let's go dance.

261
00:25:24,200 --> 00:25:25,600
-No.
-Yeah.

262
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:33,000
Thank God you broke me
out of my house.

263
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:35,600
-I know. It's about time, right?
-Yes.

264
00:25:39,400 --> 00:25:41,200
That's him, right?

265
00:25:44,200 --> 00:25:46,200
He looks super cute tonight.

266
00:25:50,600 --> 00:25:53,000
-He looks super busy to me.
-What are you talking about?

267
00:25:53,200 --> 00:25:55,800
He looks like a nice guy.
I don't think he's into her.

268
00:25:56,200 --> 00:25:57,400
I'm very sorry.

269
00:25:58,200 --> 00:25:59,800
He's breaking his neck
to get over here.

270
00:26:00,200 --> 00:26:02,400
Excuse me. Excuse me.

271
00:26:02,600 --> 00:26:04,800
May I have this dance with you?

272
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:18,800
-Can I open my eyes now?
-No, no. No, don't look.

273
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:21,200
It's worth the wait. You'll see.

274
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:30,000
Almost there. Okay, here we are.

275
00:27:30,200 --> 00:27:32,200
All right, you ready?

276
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:41,600
It looks so small.
Nothing like it feels.

277
00:27:44,800 --> 00:27:46,800
You know, sometimes
when I just feel like...

278
00:27:47,200 --> 00:27:48,800
...the whole city's
gonna swallow me up...

279
00:27:49,200 --> 00:27:51,800
...and I don't want to crawl
on all fours anymore...

280
00:27:52,600 --> 00:27:56,000
...I come up here and I feel....

281
00:27:56,400 --> 00:27:58,800
I feel like anything
can happen up here.

282
00:27:59,200 --> 00:28:04,400
I don't know, like I can lick the stars.
I can, I don't know, suck the moon.

283
00:28:04,800 --> 00:28:08,000
I could be president.

284
00:28:08,800 --> 00:28:10,800
Oh, God, I'm weird, right?

285
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:12,600
What do you wish?

286
00:28:20,600 --> 00:28:22,200
I wish that...

287
00:28:23,400 --> 00:28:25,800
...my mother was still alive.

288
00:28:30,200 --> 00:28:31,800
One day...

289
00:28:33,800 --> 00:28:35,600
...I told her that...

290
00:28:36,400 --> 00:28:39,800
...I would be the first one
in the family to be a doctor.

291
00:28:40,600 --> 00:28:42,400
A veterinarian.

292
00:28:44,200 --> 00:28:46,800
And I'll never forget...

293
00:28:50,800 --> 00:28:55,000
...she smiled at me and she said:

294
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:57,600
<i>"Paloma...</i>

295
00:28:59,000 --> 00:29:02,000
...you're gonna be the best...

296
00:29:02,800 --> 00:29:05,600
...veterinarian in the world."

297
00:29:06,200 --> 00:29:09,000
And you are. You're going to be.

298
00:29:10,200 --> 00:29:12,200
I know it. I feel it.

299
00:29:12,800 --> 00:29:14,200
No.

300
00:29:15,600 --> 00:29:17,800
Because she's gone now.

301
00:29:19,800 --> 00:29:22,400
I know, I know.

302
00:29:26,800 --> 00:29:29,600
Oh, my God, you're beautiful.

303
00:29:31,200 --> 00:29:33,600
Inside and outside.

304
00:29:42,400 --> 00:29:46,800
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. I don't know,
I couldn't help myself, I....

305
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:02,600
What?

306
00:30:03,600 --> 00:30:05,600
Come here.

307
00:30:22,800 --> 00:30:24,400
Come on, <i>Papá.</i>

308
00:30:24,800 --> 00:30:27,200
I'll help you into bed.

309
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:33,000
<i>Papá?</i>

310
00:30:39,800 --> 00:30:42,200
Yes, doctor.
Hold on one moment, please.

311
00:30:56,400 --> 00:30:58,400
-Hi, Miss Acosta?
-Yes.

312
00:30:58,800 --> 00:31:00,400
-I'm Dr. Lopez.
-Hi.

313
00:31:00,600 --> 00:31:02,800
I'm happy to say that your father's
gonna be fine.

314
00:31:03,600 --> 00:31:04,800
Thank you, doctor.

315
00:31:05,200 --> 00:31:07,200
He had a stroke,
but it was only a minor one.

316
00:31:07,600 --> 00:31:11,800
He's gonna need some extra care for
a while, but he's gonna fully recover.

317
00:31:12,200 --> 00:31:13,800
-Can I see him now?
-Yeah, sure.

318
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:15,800
-Thank you.
-This way.

319
00:31:21,600 --> 00:31:23,400
-Stop.
-I just don't know...

320
00:31:23,800 --> 00:31:26,800
...why he left his children.
That I'll never understand.

321
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:30,000
All right, all right.
You call Child Welfare...

322
00:31:30,200 --> 00:31:33,800
...and you report him.
That is what you do.

323
00:31:34,400 --> 00:31:36,000
I can't.

324
00:31:36,200 --> 00:31:38,400
You are not over him, are you?

325
00:31:38,800 --> 00:31:41,200
I am so completely over
that pig of a man.

326
00:31:42,400 --> 00:31:44,600
You know what I'm gonna do?

327
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:48,400
-I am gonna do a psychic reading.
-Oh, God, no.

328
00:31:48,600 --> 00:31:51,800
Yes, and you're gonna love it.
That's what you need right now.

329
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:53,800
-And are you ready?
-No.

330
00:31:54,800 --> 00:31:56,000
Here we go.

331
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:03,000
There's a man nearby.

332
00:32:03,400 --> 00:32:06,000
-It's giving me three clues.
-What do you mean, clues?

333
00:32:06,200 --> 00:32:08,800
Well, so that you'll recognize him
when you meet him.

334
00:32:09,200 --> 00:32:12,800
First, he will be
a great lover of music.

335
00:32:13,200 --> 00:32:14,800
Oh, that's nice.

336
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:19,800
Second, he will cherish
the colour red.

337
00:32:20,200 --> 00:32:22,000
He will serve you...

338
00:32:22,200 --> 00:32:24,800
...the greatest meal
you have ever had.

339
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:29,200
So fabulous that
you will scream with joy.

340
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:34,200
Or it might be the other way around
where you're serving him the meal.

341
00:32:34,400 --> 00:32:38,600
I don't know. But either way,
there's food involved, for sure.

342
00:32:40,200 --> 00:32:42,200
When do I meet him?

343
00:32:45,800 --> 00:32:47,000
I don't know.

344
00:32:56,200 --> 00:32:59,200
<i>Papá,</i> I was so scared.

345
00:32:59,600 --> 00:33:02,400
Nina. Nina.

346
00:33:04,400 --> 00:33:07,200
I thought I was gonna lose you too.

347
00:33:09,400 --> 00:33:11,200
Why did you even worry?

348
00:33:11,600 --> 00:33:15,800
You know I wouldn't leave you.
Not yet, anyway.

349
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:21,000
You know, Nina...

350
00:33:21,400 --> 00:33:25,200
...I died for a minute,
and guess what.

351
00:33:26,200 --> 00:33:27,800
I saw <i>Mamá.</i>

352
00:33:34,600 --> 00:33:35,800
Really?

353
00:33:38,400 --> 00:33:42,000
-How is she?
-Oh, she is doing great.

354
00:33:42,600 --> 00:33:46,000
Beautiful as ever.
And you know what else?

355
00:33:46,400 --> 00:33:50,600
She says she will wait for me
until it's my time to cross over.

356
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:55,200
And she will have a big plate
of my favourite spicy tamales...

357
00:33:55,600 --> 00:34:00,400
...just for me, so I can
smell my way to the other side.

358
00:34:00,800 --> 00:34:02,400
That's sweet, <i>Papá.</i>

359
00:34:02,600 --> 00:34:06,400
Just as long as you're not planning
on having those tamales too soon.

360
00:34:10,800 --> 00:34:13,600
<i>Mamá</i> told me it is not my time yet.

361
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:47,600
No, it was amazing.
He actually talked to his dead wife.

362
00:34:47,600 --> 00:34:50,000
No, it was amazing.
He actually talked to his dead wife.

363
00:34:50,200 --> 00:34:53,000
Well, what was that...?
How did he end up...?

364
00:34:53,400 --> 00:34:55,400
What was the communication
between them?

365
00:34:55,800 --> 00:34:57,400
It was tamales.

366
00:34:58,800 --> 00:35:00,800
-Tamales?
-Yeah.

367
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:02,200
Imagine that.

368
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:05,000
Now, let's go.

369
00:35:05,600 --> 00:35:06,800
Here we are.

370
00:35:12,600 --> 00:35:15,600
They're great, huh?
Nobody knows who they are yet.

371
00:35:16,600 --> 00:35:18,800
But they're on their way up.

372
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:23,200
That's Pancho on the guitar,
Enrique on the bass...

373
00:35:23,400 --> 00:35:25,800
...and José on the drums.

374
00:35:30,400 --> 00:35:34,600
Hey, Raj.
Raj, can I ask you something?

375
00:35:34,800 --> 00:35:36,800
How long you been together
with your girlfriend?

376
00:35:37,200 --> 00:35:40,400
My fiancée. And I've known her
for about three years.

377
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:42,600
Three years, huh?

378
00:35:43,800 --> 00:35:46,200
-Raj?
-Yep.

379
00:35:46,400 --> 00:35:49,000
How did you know
that she was the one?

380
00:35:49,400 --> 00:35:51,000
First time I saw her, I knew.

381
00:35:51,200 --> 00:35:53,000
You knew. And did she know too?

382
00:35:54,000 --> 00:35:56,800
Are you kidding? I had to chase her
around like some crazy fool.

383
00:35:57,200 --> 00:36:00,000
But you know what they say,
when a man knows, he knows.

384
00:36:00,400 --> 00:36:03,400
It's black and white for us men,
no grey stuff in between.

385
00:36:03,800 --> 00:36:05,800
Right. That's right.

386
00:36:06,800 --> 00:36:08,400
Raj.

387
00:36:09,400 --> 00:36:10,600
Last question.

388
00:36:11,600 --> 00:36:13,400
How did you hook her?

389
00:36:13,800 --> 00:36:16,000
I mean, how did you win her over?
What did you do?

390
00:36:16,600 --> 00:36:20,200
Well, I never gave up,
but I didn't crowd her either.

391
00:36:20,600 --> 00:36:22,800
I bought her a lot of beautiful gifts.

392
00:36:23,600 --> 00:36:28,000
And most importantly, I made her
confident I'd be able to provide for her.

393
00:36:28,400 --> 00:36:30,600
Women wanna know that a guy
can take care of her...

394
00:36:30,800 --> 00:36:33,000
...a guy that can really
bring home the bacon.

395
00:36:33,400 --> 00:36:35,800
I say this even though
I'm a vegetarian.

396
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:40,600
-Well, thank you.
-You're welcome.

397
00:36:40,800 --> 00:36:42,600
Okay, okay.

398
00:36:45,200 --> 00:36:48,000
Look, I hope I'm not bothering you.

399
00:36:51,400 --> 00:36:54,400
Look, I just want to give you
these flowers, that's all.

400
00:36:54,800 --> 00:36:58,200
Nothing more. No, really.

401
00:36:58,400 --> 00:36:59,600
She wouldn't believe that.

402
00:37:01,400 --> 00:37:03,800
Dr. Lopez will be here soon
to check up on you, <i>Papá.</i>

403
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:06,400
Thank you, <i>mija.</i>

404
00:37:10,200 --> 00:37:13,200
Here, let me close the curtains so you
can watch your show better.

405
00:37:13,400 --> 00:37:15,600
No, <i>mija</i>, that's okay.
I like them open.

406
00:37:16,400 --> 00:37:20,600
Look, I'm not stalking you.
No, why would l?

407
00:37:27,600 --> 00:37:30,600
See? It's better like this.

408
00:38:34,400 --> 00:38:35,400
Fuck!

409
00:38:36,200 --> 00:38:37,600
Stop!

410
00:38:45,200 --> 00:38:46,800
-What?
-What was that all about?

411
00:38:47,000 --> 00:38:48,400
-What was what all about?
-You.

412
00:38:48,800 --> 00:38:51,600
I mean, come on. The band is not
all about you and your guitar.

413
00:38:52,800 --> 00:38:55,600
I know that, it's just
we're playing with old amps. Yeah?

414
00:38:55,800 --> 00:38:58,600
You have to open them wide up
or else it doesn't sound good.

415
00:38:58,800 --> 00:39:01,200
-You should know this.
-All right. All right.

416
00:39:01,400 --> 00:39:04,200
Can we just break it down a little bit
so I could hear myself?

417
00:39:05,600 --> 00:39:09,400
One, two. One, two, three, four.

418
00:39:30,600 --> 00:39:33,400
Okay. Wait, wait. Pancho! Pancho!

419
00:39:33,800 --> 00:39:36,400
Pancho, I thought you told me
you were cool with this setup.

420
00:39:36,600 --> 00:39:38,600
You told me you were not
the lead vocalist type.

421
00:39:39,000 --> 00:39:41,400
-I never said that, man.
-Okay. Look....

422
00:39:41,600 --> 00:39:46,000
Look, we came here together
for the contest, all right?

423
00:39:46,200 --> 00:39:47,800
And exposure is something...

424
00:39:48,200 --> 00:39:50,800
...that each and every one of you
needs right now.

425
00:39:51,200 --> 00:39:53,800
So let's drop the egos...

426
00:39:54,200 --> 00:39:56,600
...and let's get out of the way
of the music, okay?

427
00:39:56,800 --> 00:39:59,400
I don't know what's wrong
with me, man. I'm sorry, man.

428
00:39:59,600 --> 00:40:01,600
I don't know what happened to me.

429
00:40:01,800 --> 00:40:04,000
I don't know what's wrong with me.

430
00:40:04,800 --> 00:40:07,200
We never had any trouble
before that guy came in.

431
00:40:07,400 --> 00:40:09,000
You know what I mean?

432
00:40:09,400 --> 00:40:11,000
I think he plays good.

433
00:40:12,600 --> 00:40:15,400
Well, yeah, I mean, the guy can play.

434
00:40:15,800 --> 00:40:17,600
But he....

435
00:40:17,800 --> 00:40:21,200
He doesn't have the mojo
that we need for the band, you know?

436
00:40:21,400 --> 00:40:22,600
Yeah.

437
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:27,600
Look, guys, just go with me
on this one, all right?

438
00:40:28,200 --> 00:40:30,600
-We're gonna win the $10,000--
-Thank you.

439
00:40:30,800 --> 00:40:32,600
I got it. We're gonna win the $10,000.

440
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:35,600
We'll open for the mystery musician.
We'll win the whole thing.

441
00:40:35,800 --> 00:40:38,200
-You just gotta trust me on this.
-I just want to play.

442
00:40:38,600 --> 00:40:40,800
We all want to play.

443
00:40:41,000 --> 00:40:42,000
-Let's do it.
-Come on.

444
00:40:49,600 --> 00:40:53,000
Hi. I came to see
how the two of you are.

445
00:40:54,600 --> 00:40:57,200
I left so many messages.

446
00:40:57,800 --> 00:40:59,400
Hi.

447
00:41:00,600 --> 00:41:03,200
I know. I'm sorry.

448
00:41:03,600 --> 00:41:06,200
I haven't been able
to return your calls.

449
00:41:06,400 --> 00:41:07,800
It's....

450
00:41:08,200 --> 00:41:10,200
I've been really busy with <i>Papá.</i>

451
00:41:10,400 --> 00:41:12,600
That's not what I meant.

452
00:41:12,800 --> 00:41:15,800
I mean, that's why I came by,
because I wanted to help you.

453
00:41:17,800 --> 00:41:22,400
Well, there's nothing
that you can really do.

454
00:41:22,600 --> 00:41:24,800
I just have to be here.

455
00:41:25,200 --> 00:41:27,800
That's why he got in trouble
in the first place...

456
00:41:28,000 --> 00:41:30,400
...because I wasn't here for him.

457
00:41:31,400 --> 00:41:34,400
But now is when you really need
your friends, right?

458
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:45,000
-I brought you something.
-No, I can't take it.

459
00:41:45,400 --> 00:41:47,600
Please, please.
I want you to have it.

460
00:41:50,000 --> 00:41:53,600
I can't. I can't be with you, Antonio.

461
00:42:01,600 --> 00:42:03,000
Why?

462
00:42:06,200 --> 00:42:08,000
I just can't.

463
00:42:09,600 --> 00:42:13,600
Please understand.
Don't make it harder on me.

464
00:42:18,400 --> 00:42:19,600
Nina...

465
00:42:22,200 --> 00:42:23,600
...I'm here for you.

466
00:42:23,800 --> 00:42:26,000
X marks the place.

467
00:42:29,600 --> 00:42:31,200
Thank you.

468
00:46:49,800 --> 00:46:51,600
-Tonio.
-Hey.

469
00:46:52,000 --> 00:46:55,600
I got some bad news. They just called.
They're not coming.

470
00:46:55,800 --> 00:46:57,600
They quit.

471
00:46:58,200 --> 00:47:00,400
-Quit?
-Yeah.

472
00:47:00,800 --> 00:47:02,600
They want to go off on their own.

473
00:47:03,800 --> 00:47:06,000
That's great. That's....

474
00:47:07,000 --> 00:47:09,600
That's great.
That's a really classy move.

475
00:47:10,000 --> 00:47:12,400
Like, three days--
Right before the tryouts!

476
00:47:12,600 --> 00:47:14,000
I know.

477
00:47:14,600 --> 00:47:17,400
Tonio. Tonio.

