00:47:18,000 --> 00:47:21,400
Come on. I'll buy you one.

479
00:47:22,000 --> 00:47:25,400
You know-- You know why? Because
he thinks he's better than me.

480
00:47:25,800 --> 00:47:27,800
He thinks because he went
to the right schools...

481
00:47:28,200 --> 00:47:29,800
...he came from
a better neighbourhood....

482
00:47:30,200 --> 00:47:31,600
Listen.

483
00:47:33,400 --> 00:47:35,000
I hear you.

484
00:47:36,400 --> 00:47:39,200
Thank you.
Thank you for giving me that.

485
00:47:39,400 --> 00:47:41,600
But it's true. He always....

486
00:47:42,800 --> 00:47:44,000
Always has all those airs.

487
00:47:44,400 --> 00:47:46,400
You guys have any requests?

488
00:47:48,600 --> 00:47:50,400
Requests?

489
00:47:53,200 --> 00:47:54,600
What do you call yourselves?

490
00:47:54,800 --> 00:47:57,200
Los Hermanos Solitos.

491
00:47:58,200 --> 00:48:00,600
"The Lonely Brothers."
Why so lonely, huh?

492
00:48:01,200 --> 00:48:03,600
-We're all single.
-We have no girlfriends, no wives.

493
00:48:03,800 --> 00:48:05,600
No problem.

494
00:48:06,600 --> 00:48:10,400
Right, that's how it is.
You have anything original?

495
00:48:10,600 --> 00:48:14,200
-Want an original? You got it.
-I always want something original.

496
00:49:18,000 --> 00:49:21,600
Javier, you wanted me to sign
the papers, I signed them.

497
00:49:22,000 --> 00:49:24,400
That's what you wanted,
that's what you got.

498
00:49:24,600 --> 00:49:27,800
-Just leave me alone.
-No way.

499
00:49:28,200 --> 00:49:30,600
But, Javier, look...

500
00:49:31,000 --> 00:49:33,600
...don't forget to be a father
to our babies, huh?

501
00:49:34,000 --> 00:49:37,400
They need that.
You just can't drop them too.

502
00:49:39,000 --> 00:49:42,000
You can't divorce your children.

503
00:49:42,200 --> 00:49:44,000
Very good.

504
00:50:03,000 --> 00:50:04,600
Antonio.

505
00:50:05,000 --> 00:50:06,200
Where have you been?

506
00:50:07,800 --> 00:50:09,200
For you.

507
00:50:09,400 --> 00:50:11,600
-They're red.
-Yes.

508
00:50:11,800 --> 00:50:14,400
I just wanted to thank you
for reminding me...

509
00:50:14,800 --> 00:50:16,800
...that my world is music.

510
00:50:18,000 --> 00:50:19,800
Antonio, I....

511
00:50:21,000 --> 00:50:24,200
-I don't deserve this.
-What, are you kidding?

512
00:50:24,400 --> 00:50:27,400
Don't ever say that. You're wonderful.
Don't doubt yourself. Here.

513
00:50:32,600 --> 00:50:36,000
-Come in.
-Oh, no, I can't. I gotta....

514
00:50:36,200 --> 00:50:38,800
I gotta go down to Los Lobos
and meet my new band.

515
00:50:40,200 --> 00:50:42,200
Do you want to come with me?

516
00:50:42,800 --> 00:50:45,800
-Oh, no. I have a lot of laundry.
-Laundry?

517
00:50:46,000 --> 00:50:49,600
And I don't have anybody
to look after my kids.

518
00:50:50,000 --> 00:50:51,400
Kids.

519
00:50:52,200 --> 00:50:53,400
But....

520
00:50:55,200 --> 00:50:57,200
Doesn't look like they'll notice.

521
00:51:01,200 --> 00:51:03,000
-Maybe next time.
-Okay.

522
00:51:03,400 --> 00:51:06,400
But these are so beautiful.

523
00:51:06,800 --> 00:51:08,000
I feel like a queen.

524
00:51:09,400 --> 00:51:11,200
That's because you are one.

525
00:51:14,400 --> 00:51:16,800
Okay. Well...

526
00:51:17,000 --> 00:51:19,000
...try to make it. Okay?

527
00:51:29,200 --> 00:51:32,200
Then all of a sudden he got mad,
picked up the mike and threw it at me.

528
00:51:32,600 --> 00:51:35,200
-And he walked out of the studio.
-Don't do live interviews.

529
00:51:35,400 --> 00:51:38,200
-I gotta. That's what I do.
-What if they don't like you?

530
00:51:38,400 --> 00:51:41,600
No, no. I just make sure
there's no sharp objects.

531
00:51:41,800 --> 00:51:43,000
-Mirabela.
-Hi.

532
00:51:43,400 --> 00:51:46,000
I'm so glad you came.
I wasn't sure if you were gonna come.

533
00:51:46,200 --> 00:51:51,400
You look beautiful. I want you to meet
my manager. Alberto, a.k.a. El Zorro.

534
00:51:53,800 --> 00:51:55,400
Thank you for coming.

535
00:51:55,600 --> 00:51:57,600
You devilish charmer, you.

536
00:51:57,800 --> 00:51:59,600
I want you to meet
the rest of the group.

537
00:51:59,800 --> 00:52:02,600
We have Rafael, <i>el guitarrón.</i>

538
00:52:03,000 --> 00:52:04,400
Welcome.

539
00:52:05,000 --> 00:52:07,200
-Adon on the percussions.
-Glad you could make it.

540
00:52:07,400 --> 00:52:08,800
-Thank you.
-A pleasure.

541
00:52:09,000 --> 00:52:11,200
And then we have here
little Jorge on lead guitar.

542
00:52:11,400 --> 00:52:13,200
Jorge. Mirabela.

543
00:52:15,000 --> 00:52:19,400
I wasn't sure if you were gonna
show up. I really started to doubt it.

544
00:52:19,800 --> 00:52:23,200
And since you're here,
why don't we...

545
00:52:25,000 --> 00:52:26,800
...take this opportunity...?

546
00:53:10,200 --> 00:53:12,200
Now you sing with me, come on.

547
00:55:45,000 --> 00:55:47,200
Nice meeting you guys.

548
00:55:47,600 --> 00:55:48,600
-I have to go.
-Why?

549
00:55:48,800 --> 00:55:51,000
-Thank you.
-What happened?

550
00:55:51,800 --> 00:55:52,800
I don't know.

551
00:55:55,800 --> 00:55:58,000
Mirabela. Mirabela, it was perfect.

552
00:55:58,400 --> 00:56:00,000
-Antonio.
-Did you hear?

553
00:56:00,200 --> 00:56:01,800
Did you hear?
You complete the band.

554
00:56:02,200 --> 00:56:03,800
Did you hear the way
the room loved you?

555
00:56:04,200 --> 00:56:05,800
It was just like my mother
used to sing.

556
00:56:08,000 --> 00:56:10,600
I'm not your mother.
I'm not that old yet.

557
00:56:10,800 --> 00:56:13,000
I know. That's not what I meant.

558
00:56:13,600 --> 00:56:16,600
-Mirabela, please. Please listen to me.
-Look.

559
00:56:18,000 --> 00:56:22,400
I'm not young or sexy anymore.

560
00:56:23,600 --> 00:56:25,200
Come on.

561
00:56:26,000 --> 00:56:27,600
Who wants to hear me sing?

562
00:56:29,400 --> 00:56:32,400
I do. I really do.

563
00:56:36,000 --> 00:56:37,400
I can't.

564
00:56:38,800 --> 00:56:40,400
I just can't.

565
00:56:42,000 --> 00:56:44,000
Oh, Mirabela.

566
00:57:55,000 --> 00:57:57,400
-ls it good?
-Oh, yeah.

567
00:57:59,200 --> 00:58:01,000
I've never seen you eat this much,
<i>Papá.</i>

568
00:58:01,200 --> 00:58:02,800
I'm a new man now.

569
00:58:03,000 --> 00:58:06,000
I feel so good that I could eat
the whole world.

570
00:58:07,400 --> 00:58:10,400
Well, you can start
with your breakfast.

571
00:58:11,400 --> 00:58:13,600
Where's that nice young man
you've been seeing?

572
00:58:14,000 --> 00:58:15,800
I haven't seen him around lately.

573
00:58:16,000 --> 00:58:17,600
Since when did you notice
such things?

574
00:58:18,200 --> 00:58:20,600
I had a dream about
the two of you last night...

575
00:58:21,200 --> 00:58:23,400
...and you were very happy together.

576
00:58:23,800 --> 00:58:25,800
Well, that's nice, but....

577
00:58:28,200 --> 00:58:30,800
I don't have time for dreams
right now.

578
00:58:32,200 --> 00:58:36,600
Our dreams are the most important
thing in this life, <i>preciosa.</i>

579
00:58:51,400 --> 00:58:52,800
Mirabela?

580
00:58:53,200 --> 00:58:55,600
Come on in. I'm back here.

581
00:58:57,600 --> 00:58:59,000
Where?

582
00:59:03,400 --> 00:59:05,400
So, what else do you do
besides laundry?

583
00:59:05,800 --> 00:59:07,800
Housecleaning.

584
00:59:09,400 --> 00:59:11,400
-Could you reach that for me?
-What thing?

585
00:59:11,600 --> 00:59:13,200
-You're so silly.
-Hey!

586
00:59:13,400 --> 00:59:15,600
What are you doing? Hey.
Give me that.

587
00:59:16,000 --> 00:59:18,200
-You want your laundry?
-Have you lost your mind?

588
00:59:18,600 --> 00:59:22,200
-No, I wanna help you regain yours.
-What are you talking about?

589
00:59:22,400 --> 00:59:24,800
-I know you really want to do this.
-Oh, God.

590
00:59:25,000 --> 00:59:26,600
What makes you think
I wanna do that?

591
00:59:26,800 --> 00:59:30,000
-I hate the thought of even doing it.
-No, you don't. You love it.

592
00:59:30,200 --> 00:59:33,000
This is part of you.
It's your whole soul.

593
00:59:33,200 --> 00:59:34,800
Oh, God.

594
00:59:36,000 --> 00:59:39,600
-What?
-I thought you were different.

595
00:59:39,800 --> 00:59:41,400
-What do you mean?
-You're like all men.

596
00:59:41,600 --> 00:59:45,200
You think that all a woman
wants to do is play house?

597
00:59:46,200 --> 00:59:49,000
Let me tell you something, okay?
I have dreams.

598
00:59:49,200 --> 00:59:51,400
Big ones. I wanna sing.

599
00:59:51,600 --> 00:59:54,200
I wanna sing in front of Javier,
that two-timing cheater...

600
00:59:54,400 --> 00:59:55,800
...in front of his girlfriend...

601
00:59:56,000 --> 00:59:58,400
...in front of everybody who thinks
I'm not thin enough.

602
00:59:58,600 --> 01:00:00,400
In front of the whole damn world.

603
01:00:04,000 --> 01:00:05,600
What is so funny?

604
01:00:06,000 --> 01:00:10,000
Oh, my God, yes.
I'm laughing at you.

605
01:00:10,600 --> 01:00:12,400
Because you're funny to me.

606
01:00:13,600 --> 01:00:15,200
Oh, yes, you are.

607
01:00:17,000 --> 01:00:19,000
You're very funny to me.

608
01:00:19,800 --> 01:00:21,600
I-- I--

609
01:00:21,800 --> 01:00:26,000
I'm gonna see you at rehearsal,
at 5:00 today. And don't be late, okay?

610
01:00:26,400 --> 01:00:28,400
Don't mix colours with whites.
It gets very muddy.

611
01:00:28,600 --> 01:00:30,600
You know how to do laundry.

612
01:00:31,800 --> 01:00:33,000
Five o'clock.

613
01:00:55,200 --> 01:00:56,800
Mirabela?

614
01:00:58,200 --> 01:01:00,800
Can I ask you something?

615
01:01:04,000 --> 01:01:07,400
I don't know. Have you ever been
truly in love?

616
01:01:08,000 --> 01:01:10,200
I'm not talking about, like, like.

617
01:01:10,400 --> 01:01:13,800
I'm talking about, like,
really, really in love?

618
01:01:14,400 --> 01:01:20,000
I thought I was with Javier,
but that was something else.

619
01:01:21,200 --> 01:01:22,800
Right, but....

620
01:01:23,600 --> 01:01:27,400
Look, but what if you
were in love now, let's say...

621
01:01:27,800 --> 01:01:30,000
...with somebody new today...

622
01:01:30,200 --> 01:01:32,000
...how would you tell them?

623
01:01:33,400 --> 01:01:34,600
Who is she, anyway?

624
01:01:36,000 --> 01:01:37,400
Well...

625
01:01:38,000 --> 01:01:40,400
...she's this woman
who doesn't know her own beauty.

626
01:01:40,600 --> 01:01:43,400
And I just--
I don't know how to tell her.

627
01:01:45,800 --> 01:01:49,200
Well, you don't tell
a woman anything...

628
01:01:49,600 --> 01:01:51,400
...just show her.

629
01:01:52,000 --> 01:01:55,600
Show her you love her.
She'll understand.

630
01:01:56,000 --> 01:02:00,000
Not in her head, but in her heart,
where it counts.

631
01:02:03,200 --> 01:02:04,600
Is that in a song somewhere?

632
01:02:06,400 --> 01:02:08,200
Hey, come on.

633
01:02:10,000 --> 01:02:11,800
You'll see. Look, look. Come on in.

634
01:02:12,400 --> 01:02:15,000
I know it. They'll love you.
Come on. You'll see.

635
01:02:15,200 --> 01:02:16,800
Mirabela!

636
01:02:18,200 --> 01:02:22,000
Hey, guys. Hey, look, I've been
working on this electronic loop and....

637
01:02:22,200 --> 01:02:24,600
Welcome to the Super Estrella
Mystery Musician tryouts.

638
01:02:24,600 --> 01:02:25,400
Welcome to the Super Estrella
Mystery Musician tryouts.

639
01:02:25,600 --> 01:02:28,200
Today's bands from all over
will battle it out...

640
01:02:28,400 --> 01:02:30,200
...to the final stage
of the competition.

641
01:02:30,600 --> 01:02:32,400
Only three lucky bands will advance.

642
01:02:32,600 --> 01:02:37,600
So let's kick it off with
band number one, Bolivar.

643
01:03:15,600 --> 01:03:17,200
What did she say?

644
01:03:17,800 --> 01:03:21,000
She said five minutes. Five times.
Is that 25 minutes?

645
01:03:21,200 --> 01:03:23,200
Okay, you can take the 5
to the 110 to the....

646
01:03:23,400 --> 01:03:26,600
<i>That was band number one, Bolivar,</i>
<i>straight out of Monterrey, Mexico.</i>

647
01:03:26,800 --> 01:03:29,000
-We can take Sepulveda.
<i>-Let's hear it for Bolivar.</i>

648
01:03:29,200 --> 01:03:32,200
-We're not gonna make it.
-Where is she?

649
01:03:32,400 --> 01:03:35,800
So keep calling in. Your votes and
our judges' votes will be tabulated.

650
01:03:36,200 --> 01:03:39,000
And up next, Las Ultrasónicas.

651
01:04:04,000 --> 01:04:06,200
I'm gonna make them late.

652
01:04:07,600 --> 01:04:10,000
-Do I look fat?
-You look fabulous.

653
01:04:10,400 --> 01:04:12,400
Mommy, you look beautiful. Honestly.

654
01:04:13,200 --> 01:04:16,800
Thank you, babies. Kiss.
Kiss, kiss.

655
01:04:17,800 --> 01:04:19,400
Enough of that.

656
01:04:20,400 --> 01:04:23,000
You listen to your mom
on the radio, okay?

657
01:04:23,800 --> 01:04:25,200
No more food.

658
01:04:25,600 --> 01:04:29,200
-Thank you. I love you.
-Good luck!

659
01:04:29,600 --> 01:04:32,200
-Here she comes. Here she comes.
-Let me see.

660
01:04:35,400 --> 01:04:36,400
You're gorgeous.

661
01:04:52,400 --> 01:04:56,000
That was Las Ultrasónicas.
It looks like you guys liked them.

662
01:04:56,400 --> 01:04:59,600
Cartel de Santa is up next.

663
01:05:39,000 --> 01:05:41,800
Where you guys been?
Come on, let's go. Come on.

664
01:05:42,200 --> 01:05:44,200
Zorro, I'm sorry.
Traffic was terrible.

665
01:05:44,400 --> 01:05:47,000
-You look great.
-Thanks. You don't think it's too tight?

666
01:05:47,400 --> 01:05:51,400
-No, no, no. Looks terrific.
-Come on, guys. Let's go.

667
01:06:11,400 --> 01:06:13,400
What an amazing group.
Cartel de Santa.

668
01:06:13,600 --> 01:06:15,400
-Let's go. Come on.
-Hurry, hurry. Come on.

669
01:06:15,800 --> 01:06:17,800
Up next, All Star Gringo Star.

670
01:07:12,000 --> 01:07:14,600
What's the matter? Come here.

671
01:07:15,200 --> 01:07:18,600
-What's the matter?
-What if they don't get me out there?

672
01:07:19,000 --> 01:07:20,800
What do you mean,
what if they don't get you?

673
01:07:21,200 --> 01:07:23,200
What if I've been lying to myself
and to everybody?

674
01:07:23,600 --> 01:07:26,400
-What if they throw things at us?
-What?

675
01:07:26,600 --> 01:07:28,400
Yeah, what if it just doesn't work?

676
01:07:28,800 --> 01:07:32,000
Listen to me. You've got it.
This is gonna be terrific.

677
01:07:32,200 --> 01:07:35,400
You're ready for this.
This is your moment. Enjoy it.

678
01:07:35,600 --> 01:07:37,800
Okay? Get ready. Come on.

679
01:07:57,800 --> 01:08:00,600
We worked really hard for this,
given it everything we've got.

680
01:08:00,800 --> 01:08:05,400
Now I want you to go out there,
be brave, be bold and honest.

681
01:08:05,800 --> 01:08:07,800
-Let's go! Go, go, go.
-Go on and have fun.

682
01:08:08,600 --> 01:08:11,600
Hello, 818. We're El Gran Colectivo.

683
01:10:45,800 --> 01:10:48,200
-Come on in.
-So is it hard being in a band?

684
01:10:48,600 --> 01:10:50,600
You know, performing in front of
all those people?

685
01:10:51,000 --> 01:10:53,200
I usually do it in front of
my family and friends...

686
01:10:53,600 --> 01:10:55,800
...but I guess there's a first time
for everything.

687
01:10:56,800 --> 01:10:59,400
-Let's not talk about it.
-You don't want to jinx it.

688
01:10:59,800 --> 01:11:01,200
-No. No.
-Thank you. Thank you.

689
01:11:01,400 --> 01:11:04,200
-No, you. You.
-You. You.

690
01:11:07,200 --> 01:11:09,200
What are you gonna do with the...?

691
01:11:09,400 --> 01:11:10,800
-How are you?
-Dr. Lopez!

692
01:11:11,000 --> 01:11:12,400
-Good to see you.
-How you feeling?

693
01:11:12,800 --> 01:11:14,400
-I feel terrific.
-You look terrific.

694
01:11:14,600 --> 01:11:16,600
-How are you?
-Hey, how are you?

695
01:11:17,000 --> 01:11:18,800
How have you been?

696
01:11:20,600 --> 01:11:23,200
You see that?
Who's that guy Nina's with?

697
01:11:23,400 --> 01:11:25,200
Some doctor.

698
01:11:26,200 --> 01:11:29,200
Looks like someone's
got Nina's attention.

699
01:11:29,400 --> 01:11:30,800
Good for him.

700
01:11:31,000 --> 01:11:32,800
What, you don't care?

701
01:11:33,600 --> 01:11:35,800
Nope. Not at all.

702
01:11:36,200 --> 01:11:37,200
Make sure you don't spill.

703
01:11:37,600 --> 01:11:40,400
You don't look like someone
who doesn't care.

704
01:11:41,200 --> 01:11:43,200
I know I know you from somewhere.

705
01:11:43,600 --> 01:11:46,600
Well, I live two blocks away from you.

706
01:11:47,000 --> 01:11:48,800
-What's your name?
-Beatriz.

707
01:11:49,000 --> 01:11:50,200
-Beatriz?
-Yeah.

708
01:11:50,600 --> 01:11:52,800
I see you almost every evening...

709
01:11:53,000 --> 01:11:55,200
...when I come back from work.

710
01:11:55,800 --> 01:11:58,400
-How do I look?
-Fantastic.

711
01:11:58,800 --> 01:12:01,200
Nina, will you help me make outfits
for the band?

712
01:12:01,400 --> 01:12:02,800
Sure.

713
01:12:04,800 --> 01:12:08,000
Zorro, I don't know, I don't know.
Nina's driving me crazy.

714
01:12:08,200 --> 01:12:11,000
My mind's on fire.
I don't know what to do.

715
01:12:13,200 --> 01:12:14,400
You'll be fine.

716
01:12:58,400 --> 01:12:59,800
-Hi.
-Hey.

717
01:13:01,000 --> 01:13:03,200
-Are you Antonio Hernandez?
-Yeah. That's me.

718
01:13:03,400 --> 01:13:04,400
What can I do for you?

719
01:13:04,600 --> 01:13:07,200
-We're from Estrella Arts Management.
-Yeah?

720
01:13:07,600 --> 01:13:09,000
We'd like to talk
about your career.

721
01:13:09,400 --> 01:13:12,000
We saw you play at the tryouts.
We think you've got potential.

